question: Jane was born on the last day of Feburary in 2000. Today is her 16-year-old birthday. What is the date today in MM/DD/YYYY?

Answer:  The question states that Jane was born on the <fact1>last day of February in 2000</fact1>.  Since February has 28 days in a non-leap year (2000 is a leap year, having 29 days, but this will be addressed next), the last day of February in 2000 was <fact1>February 29th, 2000</fact1>.  However, since 2000 was a leap year, the last day of February was February 29th. Today is her <fact2>16-year-old birthday</fact2>.  To find today's date, we add 16 years to her birthdate:  2000 + 16 = 2016.  However, since 2000 was a leap year and a 16-year span will not necessarily include another leap day falling on February 29th, we need to simply add 16 years to her birthday. Therefore, today's date is <fact2>February 28th, 2016</fact2> .  The answer is {02/28/2016}.

question: On May 9th, 2017 Jane bought 40 eggs. She ate one per day. Today she ran out of eggs. What is the date today in MM/DD/YYYY?
answer:
Reformatted Question: Jane bought <fact1>40 eggs</fact1> on <fact2>May 9th, 2017</fact2>. She ate <fact3>one per day</fact3>. <fact4>Today she ran out of eggs</fact4>. What is the date today in MM/DD/YYYY?

Answer: Jane bought <fact1>40 eggs</fact1> on <fact2>May 9th, 2017</fact2>.  Since she ate <fact3>one egg per day</fact3> and <fact4>today she ran out of eggs</fact4>,  it means 40 days have passed since May 9th, 2017.  Adding 40 days to May 9th, 2017:

May has 31 days.  From May 9th to May 31st is 22 days (31 - 9 = 22).
40 days - 22 days = 18 days remaining.

June has 30 days.  Since we have 18 days remaining, we don't reach the end of June. Therefore today's date is June 18th, 2017.

The date today is {06/18/2017}.
